body:
This improves plugin association resolution to support using associations to ignore certain paths for certain plugins.

For example, in the following example both the typescript and prettier plugin format `.ts` and `.js` files. This PR enables not formatting only `.js` files with the typescript plugin by only having a negated glob.

```jsonc
{
  "typescript": {
    "associations": [
      "!**/*.js" // don't format javascript files with this plugin
    ]
  },
  "includes": [
    "**/*.*"
  ],
  "plugins": [
    "https://plugins.dprint.dev/typescript-0.78.0.wasm",
    "https://plugins.dprint.dev/prettier-0.13.0.json@dc5d12b7c1bf1a4683eff317c2c87350e75a5a3dfcc127f3d5628931bfb534b1"
  ]
}
```

Additionally, this PR fixes a bug where plugins with "associations" were matching based on a file name or extension if no other plugin matched the association.

